args: Mitsuba or Nazuna...\nWho's going to win?
Well, I guess that's it, Nazuna.
I plated quickly, my garnishes were\nimpeccable, my recipes were novel...\nI was superior in so many ways, so why?
If you listened to the guests, you'd know.
Everyting was delicious, but... Hmm, how\nto put this? Nanakusa's food was...warm.
Hey, yeah, that's exactly it! I took my\ntime eating, but the food didn't get cold!
That was pretty strange, huh? Hey, wait.\nDon't these plates actually seem warm?
Lemme see... Ah, you're right! All their\nplates are warmed! How thorough of them!
Wait, you warmed the actual plates?
Yep. I've matched the temperature of the\nplates to the food that will go on them.

It prevents the food from cooling, while not
overheating it, ensuring the guest can
enjoy their food at the proper temperature
all the way to the last bite.
Are you KIDDING me?! You made sure\nyour PLATES were temperature-matched?\nThat's idiotic!
Worrying about that sort of thing\nis incredibly inefficient.
No wonder business at Nanakusa is\noff-track!
The spirit of hospitality I embody is rooted\nin making every meal I serve into a rich,\nfulfilling experience from top to bottom.
That's the definition of ＂service with soul.＂
Listen up, girls. A restaurant like ours is\na place where customers come to eat on\noccasions they hold dear.
That's why as chefs, we must value our\ncustomers' time as much as they do.

Even when you aren't waiting on them
directly, our hospitality is what turns mere
food into a rich, fulfilling experience.
That is the definition of ＂service with soul.＂
No. But Mitsuba, I admit defeat.
Inheriting father's technique alone isn't the\nsame as inheriting the soul of Nanakusa.
I got so wrapped up in my own path to\nsave our family restaurant that I guess\nI lost sight of what really matters.
Yeah. I'm not going to buy out Nanakusa.
Instead, I'd like to propose a\nbusiness partnership.
*sigh* Exactly what it sounds like, sis.\nIs your brain only good for cooking?
I'm saying I'll give you money! Which\nmeans you can focus on rebuilding the\nNanakusa school of cooking YOUR way.
Bear in mind that I have high standards\nfor my business partners! I'm gonna need\nyou to get things back on track ASAP.
O-of course! And, um... Thank you.
Don't sweat it. Our methods may differ,\nbut we clearly both love our family.
Oh, and speaking of family, they said to\nstop acting all hoity-toity and to come\nhome for a visit one of these days.
They're really worried about you, y'know.
Heh. I bet they are. I'll be sure to drop in\nand update them on my training soon.
(We're all dreamers, us Nanakusa kids.\nMitsuba most of all.)
(Just what is it that keeps me\nfrom getting to her level?)
Everything was delicious today.\nI can rest easy knowing that the\nrestaurant AND Mitsuba are both back.
Glad to hear it. I'll be packing up and\nheading back to Alberia soon to keep\nhoning my technique, though!
Aha ha! Like father, like daughter. He, too,\nwas always on some new culinary quest.\nI'll be looking forward to your return.
(Father... Thanks to Nazuna's help,\nNanakusa's customer base is slowly\nreturning to what it once was.)
(I haven't surpassed you yet, but mark\nmy words—that day is coming soon.)
Watch over me until then, Father. I vow to\nuphold the ideals of ＂service with soul＂!
